text.b: Woodmont Country Club – LUPA Traffic Statement

page.text: Land Design South (LDS) has been retained to evaluate the traffic impact for the proposed Land Use Plan
Amendment (LUPA) at the Woodmont Country Club property. The project encompasses 39.69 acres as a result
of the shortening of the existing golf courses from 36 holes to 27 holes. As shown in Table 1, The Applicant is
proposing land use plan changes on seven (7) parcels, from the current Commercial Recreation land use designation
The purpose of this analysis is to evaluate the traffic impact of the proposed land use changes to seven (7) parcels
and to determine compliance with the City of Tamarac and the Broward County Comprehensive Plan – Transportation
The seven (7) parcels are located within the Woodmont Country Club, bound by Southgate Boulevard to the
north, McNab Road to the south, Pine Island Road to the west and University Drive to the east, in the City of
Tamarac, Broward County, Florida. Property ID Numbers associated with this project are: 4941-04-26-0010 /

credit was taken for the golf course trip generation.

under the Proposed Future Land Use designations for the seven (7) parcels.
